This paper deals with information theory and specifically with the entropy of data elements. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the behavior of entropy under transformations, which could fall under cs.IS (Information Systems) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper uses mathematical analysis to prove its results, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
